<HEADLINE> Bus Plunges Into Bangladesh River  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) -- Rescuers recovered 13 bodies Sunday and
were searching for another 37 passengers feared drowned when their
bus plunged into a river the day before.
</P>
<P>
   The bus driver lost control Saturday while steering the bus onto
a ferry in Pirojpur district in southern Bangladesh, Police Chief
Mohammad Nasiruddin said.
</P>
<P>
   Fifty-five people were on the bus, many of them students. Five
people escaped by going through open windows.
</P>
<P>
   Rescuers found 13 bodies floating in the river Sunday,
Nasiruddin said. A salvage ship pulled out the bus Sunday but no
bodies were found inside, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The rescue operation was delayed as police took hours to reach
the accident site, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
   Pirojpur district is located 85 miles south of Dhaka.
</P>
</TEXT>
