<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-28 16:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Charged in TV Personality Slay  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- British police on Sunday charged a man with the
murder of television personality Jill Dando, more than a year after
she was gunned down on the doorstep of her London home.
</P>
<P>
   A Scotland Yard spokeswoman said that Barry Michael George, also
known as Barry Bulsara, had been charged with killing the popular
TV newscaster and would appear before West London Magistrates Court
early on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   George, an unemployed 40-year-old who lived in the same west
London district as Dando, had been held for questioning since
police raided his home on Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
   Under British law, police can detain a suspect for 24 hours
without charge. Further extensions can be granted up to 96 hours.
Police had received three extensions allowing them to hold George
until 11 p.m. local time Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   George had legally changed his name to Bulsara, reportedly in
admiration of the late Queen singer Freddie Mercury, whose original
surname was Bulsara.
</P>
<P>
   Dando, 37, was shot in the head at point-blank range as she
returned home from shopping errands in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
   She had appeared on news and current affairs programs for the
British Broadcasting Corp., and was popular among audiences.
</P>
<P>
   Police floated several theories about the murder, speculating
that Dando might have been killed by an obsessive stalker or
targeted by a hitman as a result of her involvement in the program
''Crimewatch,'' which appeals to the public for help in solving
real-life crimes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-28-00 1652 </TRAILER>
