<HEADLINE> Jockey Prado Gets 4,000th Win  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Jockey Edgar Prado rode his 4,000th winner
Sunday, guiding Thunder Breeze to victory by a neck over
Mylittlevic in the second race at Belmont Park.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a big accomplishment,'' said Prado, a 32-year-old
native of Lima, Peru. ''Throughout the years I've had a lot of
support from trainers and owners.''
</P>
<P>
   Prado, who led the United States with 402 victories last year,
is the 42nd jockey to collect at least 4,000 career winner.
</P>
<P>
   Thunder Breeze covered the six furlongs in 1 minute, 11.39
seconds and paid $3.20, $2.50 and $2.10 in the $16,500 claiming
race.
</P>
<P>
   Mylittlevic, with Filiberto Leon aboard, paid $4.70 and $2.70.
</P>
<P>
   Lambourne was 2} lengths back in third place and paid $2.40.
</P>
<P>
   In Belmont Park's Sunday feature, Gone Fishin beat Weatherbird
by 2{ lengths in the 17th running of the $87,150 Jaipur Stakes.
French Envoy was third.
</P>
<P>
   Gone Fishin, with John Velazquez aboard, covered the seven
furlongs in 1:21.3 to earn $52,290 for Dogwood Stable and win for
the second time in four starts this year. The horse returned
$13.00, $6.70 and $4.80.
</P>
<P>
   Weatherbird paid $17.20 and $12.40, and French Envoy $10.60.
</P>
</TEXT>
