<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian-Bred Riboletta Wins Milady  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Brazilian-bred Riboletta, the favorite
ridden by Chris McCarron, beat Bordelaise by three lengths Sunday
in the $203,000 Milady Breeders' Cup Handicap at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   The 5-year-old mare carried 120 pounds and was pressed on the
lead throughout the 1[ miles. Riboletta shook off bids turning for
home from both Bordelaise and Excellent Meeting before drawing off
to win in 1:42.
</P>
<P>
   She paid $4, $2.60 and $2.10.
</P>
<P>
   The win was the ninth in 22 career starts for Riboletta and the
winning purse of $112,860 improved her career earnings to $574,953.
</P>
<P>
   Bordelaise returned $3.80 and $2.40, while Excellent Meeting was
another length back in third in the field of six and paid $2.10 to
show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
