<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minor Damage at N.H. Abortion Clinic  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CONCORD, N.H. (AP) -- A fire caused minor damage at an abortion
clinic Sunday night. The clinic was closed at the time and no one
was inside.
</P>
<P>
   The cause was under investigation but police Sgt. Lionel Talbot
said ''we're treating it as suspicious.''
</P>
<P>
   Firefighters who arrived at The Concord Feminist Health Center
shortly after 10 p.m. saw a few flames outside along the basement
wall, said fire Lt. Tony Manning.
</P>
<P>
   The fire damaged aluminum siding, and Manning said there was
smoke damage inside.
</P>
<P>
   Manning could not say if the fire was set. He also said he did
not know where it started, except that most of the fire damage
appeared to be to the back exterior wall of the 2{-story building.
</P>
<P>
   The center has been the target of a number of protests by
abortion opponents.
</P>
</TEXT>
